Percutaneous balloon valvotomy for the treatment of isolated tricuspid stenosis.
 A 46-year-old woman with isolated tricuspid stenosis complained of increasing fatigue and dyspnea on exertion.
 Exercise Doppler echocardiography reproduced her symptoms and revealed a marked increase in trans-tricuspid gradient.
 Successful percutaneous balloon tricuspid valvotomy was performed, with resolution of her symptoms.
